      <!-- Auth model -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Auth</div>
          <h2>One API-key model across every surface.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            Every surface authenticates with a prefixed secret key. Prefix encodes environment and
            blast radius; <code>require_principal</code> in the API gateway hashes the key (SHA-256),
            looks up the owning merchant/agent, and attaches a principal to the request for the
            orchestrator to consume.
          </p>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Prefix</th><th>Environment</th><th>Use</th><th>Rotation</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>sk_live_…</code></td><td>Production</td><td>Real money, real compliance, real rate limits.</td><td>Hot-rotatable from dashboard; old key decays 24h.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>sk_test_…</code></td><td>Sandbox</td><td>Policy &amp; mandate logic end-to-end, but settlement is simulated.</td><td>Self-serve in dashboard.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>sk_dev_…</code></td><td>Local</td><td>Emitted by <code>sardis auth login</code> against local API.</td><td>Never leaves laptop.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>pk_live_…</code></td><td>Public / client</td><td>Checkout, spend widget — rate-limited, read-biased scope only.</td><td>Safe to embed.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Python SDK -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">01 · Python SDK</div>
          <h2><code>sardis-sdk</code> — async httpx client.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            Lives at <code>packages/sardis-sdk-python/</code>. Async is the default
            (<code>AsyncSardisClient</code>); sync exists for scripts. Connection pooling, retry with
            exponential backoff, token refresh, and typed errors are built-in.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="mt-16">Install &amp; quickstart</h3>
        <pre><code># install
pip install sardis-sdk
# or
uv add sardis-sdk

# set API key
export SARDIS_API_KEY=sk_live_…</code></pre>

        <p class="mt-16 text-muted">
          From <code>packages/sardis-sdk-python/examples/quickstart.py</code> — the canonical flow:
          create agent → create wallet → parse a natural-language policy → pay → check balance.
        </p>
        <pre><code>import asyncio, os
from sardis_sdk import AsyncSardisClient

async def main():
    async with AsyncSardisClient(api_key=os.environ["SARDIS_API_KEY"]) as client:
        agent   = await client.agents.create(name="My First Agent")
        wallet  = await client.wallets.create(agent_id=agent.agent_id, chain="base")

        policy  = await client.policies.parse(
            text="Max $100 per transaction, $500 per day, no gambling",
        )
        await client.policies.apply(wallet_id=wallet.wallet_id, policy=policy)

        payment = await client.payments.send(
            wallet_id=wallet.wallet_id,
            to="merchant_demo",
            amount="25.00",
            purpose="API usage - OpenAI",
        )
        print(payment.status, payment.tx_id)

        balance = await client.wallets.get_balance(wallet.wallet_id)
        print(balance.balance, balance.currency)

asyncio.run(main())</code></pre>

